Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo In a bid to ensure quality service delivered, the Management of University of Osun Teaching Hospital, Osogbo, has instituted a service delivery monitoring committee. The Chief Medical Director of the hospital, Prof. Peter Olaitan, said this during an inter-religious prayer session in Osogbo. A statement by the Public Relations Officer of the hospital, Ayodele Adeyemo, quoted the CMD as saying that commendations and sanctions by the committee would be appropriately applied. The CMD also implored members of staff of the hospital to be professional and to ensure that patients were promptly and respectfully attended to. The statement read in part, “To ensure quality service is delivered, the CMD disclosed that the management has instituted a service delivery monitoring committee. He assured that commendations and sanctions will be appropriately applied as may be necessary from time to time. “In appreciating Governor Oyetola for giving attention to requests from the Management of the hospital, Prof. Olaitan said Staff should be excited about the recent development which brought about the change in the name of the hospital to UniOsun Teaching Hospital Osogbo and see it as a good omen.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 